### 1. Get all tasks
GET http://localhost:8000/tasks

### 2. Get a single task
GET http://localhost:8000/tasks/1

### 3. Get a task that does not exist
GET http://localhost:8000/tasks/999

### 4. Create a new task (valid)
POST http://localhost:8000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Finish Assignment",
  "description": "Testing POST request",
  "user_id": 1
}

### 5. Create a task with missing title
POST http://localhost:8000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": 1
}

### 6. Create a task with invalid user_id
POST http://localhost:8000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Invalid User Task",
  "user_id": 999
}

### 7. Update a task
PUT http://localhost:8000/tasks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "completed": true
}

### 8. Delete a task
DELETE http://localhost:8000/tasks/2

### 9. Get tasks for a specific user
GET http://localhost:8000/users/1/tasks
